    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1949-11-29T14:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1949-11-29T14:00:00-05:00" n="222"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d222">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.01/11–2949: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Bruce</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1949-11-29T20:00:00+01:00"
                            >November 29, 1949—8 p. m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received 11 p. m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5022. Foreign Office confirms information given London’s 933, November 28,<note
                        n="48" xml:id="d222fn48">Same as telegram No. 4731, November 28, 5 p. m.,
                        from London, <ref target="#pg_203">p. 203</ref>.</note> regarding Vatican’s
                    desire extend early recognition Chinese Communists. Foreign Office states
                    Vatican reluctant to take lead, however, and is endeavoring to persuade some
                    prominent Catholic country break the ice. French position, however, remains
                    unchanged (Embtel 4790, November 16).</p>
                <p>Sent Department 5022, repeated London 876.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bruce</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
